  "prompt": "What are the best schools in Hyderabad for 8th class?",
  "response": "Hyderabad has several excellent schools for students entering the 8th grade. Some of these schools are well-known for their academic rigor, extracurricular activities, facilities, and overall child development. Here's a list of some of the reputed schools in Hyderabad:\n\n1. **DPS Hyderabad (Delhi Public School)**\n   - Known for academic excellence, comprehensive curriculum, and extracurricular activities.\n\n2. **Oakridge International School**\n   - Follows IB and CBSE curriculums, with emphasis on holistic development.\n\n3. **Chirec International School**\n   - Offers CBSE, IB, and Cambridge curricula, strong emphasis on academics and extracurriculars.\n\n4. **Jubilee Hills Public School**\n   - CBSE curriculum, good infrastructure, and academic record.\n\n5. **The Hyderabad Public School (HPS)**\n   - One of the oldest and most prestigious institutions, offers ISC and Cambridge curricula.\n\n6. **Silver Oaks International School**\n   - Focuses on values-based education and offers both CBSE and IB curricula.\n\n7. **International School of Hyderabad**\n   - Offers international curriculum, promoting global education standards.\n\n8. **Glendale Academy**\n   - CBSE curriculum, known for academic curriculum and extra-curricular activities.\n\n9. **Sreenidhi International School**\n   - IB curriculum, promotes experiential learning and holistic development.\n\n10. **Gitanjali School**\n    - Multiple branches in the city, follows ICSE curriculum, known for academic excellence.\n\n11. **Sloka - The Hyderabad Waldorf School**\n    - Offers Waldorf education, focuses on creative and experiential learning.\n\nChoosing the best school depends on various factors such as location, curriculum preference, individual needs and priorities. It's advisable to visit the schools, meet the teachers, understand the environment, and review their policies and achievements before making a decision.",
